    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Webhook Authorization Methods\n\nThere are 2 major types of Authorization for Webhooks:\n\n###  1️⃣ **Basic Authentication**\n\n* Credentials are passed in a base64-encoded format.\n* ⚠️ **Note:** Embedding credentials in the URL is discouraged due to security risks.\n\nHeader Example:\nAuthorization: Basic 123456789\n\n### 2️⃣ **Bearer Authorization (API Key)**\n\n* The API key (token) is **not included in the URL**, but sent in the header.\n* Common for securing API endpoints.\n\n**Example Request:**\nGET https://n8n.ai-boostbrands.com/webhook-test/login\n\nAuthorization: Bearer <API_KEY>\n\n### 3️⃣ **Header Authorization (OAuth 2.0)**\n\n* When redirecting to an OAuth 2.0 authorization server, the token is passed securely in the header.\n\nAuthorization: <access_token>\n\n\n---\n\n### 4️⃣ **JWT (JSON Web Tokens)**\n\n* Functions similarly to Bearer tokens.\n* The JWT is passed in the `Authorization` header.\n\nAuthorization: Bearer <JWT_token>\n\n\n",
        "width": 1040,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1380,
        0
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
