    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "Notify Slack upon new onboarding form submission\n\n## Bot Registration Methods\n\n1️⃣ Access Token Method\n\nYou obtain an access token and use it directly for API operations.\n\n2️⃣ OAuth 2.0 Flow (Redirect URL + Client ID)\n\nStandard, secure method involving user authorization.\nMore secure, suited for public or multi-user applications.\n\n1️⃣ OAuth & Permissions\nRequired for connecting Slack with N8N or other automation tools.\n\n2️⃣ Event Subscriptions\nAllows your bot to respond to Slack events in real-time.\n\nExamples of events:\nNew message in a channel\nUser joins a workspace\nReactions added\n\nSteps to Enable For webhook:\n\nProvide a public, verified Webhook URL\nSlack sends event payloads to this URL\nYour bot processes and responds accordingly\n\n",
